      "source": [
        "# Projectile Motion\n",
        "\n",
        "**Topic:** Physics - Kinematics\n",
        "\n",
        "Analyze how projectiles follow different trajectories based on launch angles. Compare the range and height for 30deg, 45deg, and 60deg launch angles using physics equations.\n",
        "\n",
        "## \ud83d\udcd6 Instructions\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Run the code** by clicking the \u25b6\ufe0f button or pressing Shift+Enter\n",
        "2. **Review the output** - graphs, calculations, and visualizations\n",
        "3. **Modify the code** - change values and re-run to experiment\n",
        "4. **Try the challenges** at the bottom of this lesson\n",
        "\n",
        "---"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "print(\" PROGRAM NAME : Projectile Motion Analysis \")\n",
        "print()\n",
        "\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# =================================\n",
        "# FORMULA CONSTANTS\n",
        "# =================================\n",
        "g = 9.81  # Acceleration due to gravity (m/s^2)\n",
        "v = 40    # Initial velocity (m/s)\n",
        "angles = [30, 45, 60]  # Launch angles (degrees)\n",
        "\n",
        "# =================================\n",
        "# PHYSICS FORMULAE\n",
        "# =================================\n",
        "# Position Equations:\n",
        "# x(t) = v0 * cos(theta) * t          [horizontal distance]\n",
        "# y(t) = v0 * sin(theta) * t - 0.5*g*t^2   [vertical distance/height]\n",
        "#\n",
        "# Time of Flight: T = (2 * v\u2080 * sin(\u03b8)) / g\n",
        "# Range (max distance): R = (v0^2 * sin(2*theta)) / g\n",
        "# Maximum Height: H = (v0^2 * sin^2(theta)) / (2g)\n",
        "\nprint(\"Analysis of Projectile Motion\")\nprint(\"=\"*60)\nprint(f\"Initial Velocity: {v} m/s\")\nprint(f\"Gravity: {g} m/s^2")\nprint(\"=\"*60)\nprint()\n\n# =================================\n# CALCULATE TRAJECTORIES\n# =================================\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 7))\n\nfor angle in angles:\n    theta = np.radians(angle)  # Convert angle to radians\n    \n    # Calculate time of flight\n    t_flight = (2 * v * np.sin(theta)) / g\n    \n    # Create time array\n    t = np.linspace(0, t_flight, num=100)\n    \n    # Calculate x and y positions\n    x = v * np.cos(theta) * t\n    y = v * np.sin(theta) * t - 0.5 * g * t**2\n    \n    # Calculate range and max height\n    range_dist = (v**2 * np.sin(2 * theta)) / g\n    max_height = (v**2 * np.sin(theta)**2) / (2 * g)\n    \n    # Print results\n    print(f\"Launch Angle: {angle}\u00b0\")\n    print(f\"  Range (R):           {range_dist:.2f} m\")\n    print(f\"  Time of Flight (T):  {t_flight:.2f} s\")\n    print(f\"  Maximum Height (H):  {max_height:.2f} m\")\n    print()\n    \n    # Plot the trajectory\n    plt.plot(x, y, marker='o', linestyle='-', linewidth=2.5, \n             label=f'{angle}\u00b0 (R={range_dist:.1f}m)', markersize=4, alpha=0.8)\n\n# =================================\n# FORMATTING\n# =================================\nplt.title('Projectile Motion for Different Launch Angles', \n          fontweight='bold', fontsize=14, pad=20)\nplt.xlabel('Horizontal Distance (m)', fontweight='bold', fontsize=12)\nplt.ylabel('Height (m)', fontweight='bold', fontsize=12)\nplt.legend(fontsize=11, loc='upper right', framealpha=0.95)\nplt.grid(True, alpha=0.3, linestyle='--')\nplt.xlim(0, 170)\nplt.ylim(0, 65)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()\n\nprint(\"=\"*60)\nprint(\"\u2705 Analysis complete!\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## \ud83c\udfaf Physics Concepts\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Key Equations**\n",
        "\n",
        "**Position:**\n",
        "- x(t) = v0 cos(theta) * t\n",
        "- y(t) = v0 sin(theta) * t - 0.5*g*t^2\n",
        "\n",
        "**Maximum Values:**\n",
        "- **Range:** R = (v0^2 * sin(2*theta)) / g\n",
        "- **Time of Flight:** T = (2*v0 * sin(theta)) / g\n",
        "- **Maximum Height:** H = (v0^2 * sin^2(theta)) / (2g)\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Important Observations**\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **45deg gives maximum range** when launch and landing heights are equal\n",
        "2. **30deg and 60deg** produce the same range (complementary angles)\n",
        "3. **Steeper angles** reach higher but land closer\n",
        "4. **Flatter angles** travel farther but lower\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## \ud83d\udcdd Try These Experiments\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Change the initial velocity:**\n",
        "   ```python\n",
        "   v = 30  # or 50, 60, etc.\n",
        "   # How does this affect range and flight time?\n",
        "   ```\n",
        "\n",
        "2. **Add more angles:**\n",
        "   ```python\n",
        "   angles = [15, 30, 45, 60, 75]\n",
        "   # Find all pairs with equal range!\n",
        "   ```\n",
        "\n",
        "3. **Change gravity (simulate other planets):**\n",
        "   ```python\n",
        "   g = 1.62   # Moon\n",
        "   g = 3.71   # Mars\n",
        "   g = 24.79  # Jupiter\n",
        "   ```\n",
        "\n",
        "4. **Calculate energy:**\n",
        "   ```python\n",
        "   mass = 1  # kg\n",
        "   KE = 0.5 * mass * v**2\n",
        "   PE = mass * g * max_height\n",
        "   ```\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "**Happy Learning!** \ud83c\udf89"
      ]
    }
